page.title: 02HAMBURY TOUT
page.content: {HAMBURY TOUT}is the highest point in our area.It is 441 feet above sea level.From the top,you can see in all directions. To the NORTH,there is the Durdle Door Caravan Park and a large expanse of farmland, belonging to Newlands Farm. To the WEST is Durdle Door. To the SOUTH is Lulworth Cove and the sea. To the EAST is Bindon Hill and West Lulworth. On the top of Hambury Tout, there is a burial mound or round barrow. Various remains, including a skeleton were discovered, when there was an excavation in 1790.
